Name: frontal sinusitis
Definition: A sinusitis which involves infection of the frontal sinuses over the eyes in the brow area. This causes pain or pressure in the frontal sinus cavity and headache over the forehead.

Name: sphenoid sinusitis
Definition: A sinusitis which involves infection of sphenoid sinuses that causes pain or pressure behind the eyes

Name: obsolete congenital syphilitic encephalitis
Definition: A sinusitis which involves infection of sphenoid sinuses that causes pain or pressure behind the eyes

Name: maxillary sinusitis
Definition: A sinusitis which involves infection of maxillary sinuses that causes pain or pressure over the cheeks just below the eyes

Name: ethmoid sinusitis
Definition: A sinusitis which involves infection of ethmoid sinuses that causes pain or pressure behind and between the eyes

Name: obsolete toxic myopathy
Definition: A sinusitis which involves infection of ethmoid sinuses that causes pain or pressure behind and between the eyes
